Conductor Leonard Bernstein has canceled several

performances in Japan due to exhaustion and lingering illness and will return to the United States to recover, his manager announced today.
"Leonard Bernstein is suffering from exhaustion as a result of trying to fulfill his professional obligations while not having fully recovered from several ailments he suffered this spring.
Bernstein, 71, has suffered from severe influenza, pleurisy, and pneumonia since the beginning of the year, Cahill said in a statement released by Harry Kraut, Bernstein's manager.
Bernstein issued a separate statement apologizing to his fans and sponsors and saying that he had asked LSO principal conductor Michael Tilson Thomas and Japanese conductor Eiji Oue to fulfill his conducting responsibilities.
